# Connecting Your Clarity Call Project to MongoDB Compass

I'll guide you through the steps to connect your project to MongoDB Compass so your data can be stored properly.

## Step 1: Install MongoDB Compass

1. Download MongoDB Compass from the official website: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/compass
2. Install it on your computer by following the installation wizard

## Step 2: Install MongoDB Server (if not already installed)

1. Download MongoDB Community Server: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community
2. Install it, making sure to select "Install MongoDB as a Service" during installation
3. Complete the installation process

## Step 3: Update Your Project's .env File

Make sure your .env file has the correct MongoDB connection string:
```properties
PORT=3000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/clarity_call
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_key_change_this_in_production
```